    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the North Dakota 7-month rule?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The 7-month rule is North Dakota's statutory residence test. If you maintain a permanent place of abode in the state and spend in the aggregate more than seven months, which the state equates to 210 days, of the tax year in North Dakota, you must file as a full-year resident even if you were domiciled in another state."
