      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you need a home in Pennsylvania to be a statutory resident?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The statutory residence test requires both a permanent place of abode in Pennsylvania and more than 183 days in the state. Days alone, without a qualifying place of abode, do not make you a statutory resident, though separate domicile rules can."
